@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor Student
actor "Assignment-owning Lecturer" as Lecturer
actor Admin

rectangle EduSecure {
  usecase "Authenticate" as UC1
  usecase "Complete MFA Challenge" as UC2
  usecase "Submit Assignment" as UC3
  usecase "Review Submission\nIntegrity Status" as UC4
  usecase "Create / Update Grade" as UC5
  usecase "Review Audit Trail" as UC6
}

Student --> UC1
Student --> UC2
Student --> UC3

Lecturer --> UC1
Lecturer --> UC4
Lecturer --> UC5

Admin --> UC1
Admin --> UC4 : oversight
Admin --> UC5 : oversight
Admin --> UC6

UC2 ..> UC1 : <<extends>> when MFA is enabled
UC5 ..> UC6 : <<logs>>

note bottom of EduSecure
This simplified use-case diagram is intended for the final report.
It keeps the focus on the implemented security controls:
MFA, role-restricted submission review, grade integrity,
and audit-backed accountability.
end note
@enduml

